newsitem.title: USA: CBOT soybeans, soymeal rally on USDA data, funds.
newsitem.headline: CBOT soybeans, soymeal rally on USDA data, funds.

text.p: Gains were extended late in CBOT soybean and soymeal futures trading with most contracts in fast dealings on bullish input from USDA's supply and demand data, traders said.
Stops were hit in March soybeans above $7.61 per bushel. Traders said Refco Inc and Lee B. Stern were major buyers of soybeans.
Funds were active buyers of soymeal and stops were hit above $246.00 per ton in the March, traders said.
"Funds bought 5,000 or 6,000 (lots) soymeal," a floor source said.
USDA on Wednesday trimmed its projection for U.S. ending soybean stocks to 140 million bushels from 155 million in January's report.
At 1311 CST, soybeans were up 15 to 2-1/2 cents per bushel with March up 15 at $7.64-3/4.
Soymeal was up $5.90 to $2.30 per ton with March up $5.90 at $248.00
